body:
I cannot seem to get the whisper event to work.  My current code has a near copy of the example whisper code.  I'm thinking their is a problem with the API but I'm not an expert in JavaScript.

My Code: http://pastebin.com/JdsYB9jz

comment_data.body: Mineflayer uses the `/tell` command. Is that implemented on `woodycraft.net`?
Also the chat might not be parsed correctly. Does the `whisper` event get emitted, i.e. does the console print `"I received a message from ..."`? Or does the bot just not chat back?
Usually these servers have custom messages. I usually had to do bot.on("message"...) (or whichever one brought back JSON or just plain text) and then regex it.

@Gjum WoodyCraft does support the /tell command but I don't receive the console output,

@demipixel I'll give that a try.  Thank you.
@JustinKelleher also take a look at #323 #273 and maybe #175
@Gjum Thanks!  I'm confused on how to use the chat pattern system but I'll try it out.

Yeah you might want to look at the example for chat pattern https://github.com/andrewrk/mineflayer/blob/master/examples/chatAddPattern.js

Bukkit minecraft servers use different chat plugins, so some work has to be done to parse the specific format for each server.

@JustinKelleher You have that problem because mineflayer cannot parse any server's private message format, so you should listen on "message" and write your own parser.

*edit: @rom1504 was faster :)*

Why does the regex statement return the username as "null"?

https://gist.github.com/JustinKelleher/b06fb5c29e137c4284e1
Seems the problem was fixed in that gist, feel free to reopen if you have more problem about that !
